<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>530 and DT-466/408 Diesel Engine Service (1994) - ROCKER ARM ASSEMBLY, CAMSHAFT, TAPPETS AND PUSH RODS -
        CAMSHAFT, TAPPETS &#38; PUSH RODS - CAMSHAFT BUSHING INSPECTION
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="1">
        <title>CAMSHAFT BUSHING INSPECTION</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the four camshaft bushings for wear and proper running clearance as follows:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Measure camshaft bushing journal diameter using a micrometer. Measure at two locations
                    (at 90&#176;) and record the readings.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Using a telescoping gauge and micrometer, measure the camshaft bushing I.D. with bushing
                    installed in the crankcase. Record the readings.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Subtract the readings obtained in steps 1 a and b, to determine running clearance.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">maximum allowable running clearance is exceeded (see "
                    <emph type="bold">SPECIFICATIONS</emph>"), replace the camshaft bushings using the camshaft bushing
                    remover and installer (
                    <emph type="bold">ZTSE2893A</emph>).
                </para>
                <figure id="ef1050522" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg11269" filename="../figcg1/CG11269.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 5.22.</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <important>
                        <para>WHEN SERVICING THE CAMSHAFT BUSHINGS, THE CRANKSHAFT AND MAIN BEARING MUST BE REMOVED FROM
                            THE CRANKCASE TO AVOID DEBRIS CONTAMINATION.
                        </para>
                    </important>
                </specpara>
            </step2>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
